<p class="article-lead">To ship perfume samples internationally, first confirm that the carrier accepts the actual alcohol-based product on the intended route. A small parcel is still subject to transport restrictions.</p><p>Provide the destination, sample size, number of vials, formula or SDS information and declared purpose. The logistics provider determines suitable service, packing, marks and documents. Avoid misdeclaring perfume as a non-hazardous cosmetic; rejection, return or enforcement can cost more than compliant shipping.</p><p>{{config.brand.name}}'s standard evaluation set is {{config.samples.setDisplay}}. Samples are free, while the buyer pays the actual courier charge confirmed before dispatch. Preparation generally takes {{config.samples.preparationDays.display}} after the brief and delivery details are complete.</p>
